                            <comment id="12990661" author="rding" created="Fri, 4 Feb 2011 18:13:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Review comments are here &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/321/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/321/&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since the review board hasn&apos;t been linked with Jira, please upload the new patch to the jira.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As for the &apos;include&apos; statement, a related jira is &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1824&quot; title=&quot;Support import modules in Jython UDF&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1824&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-1824&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; where the idea is to add SHIP clause so Pig would ship &apos;import/include&apos; scripts to the backend.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
